Comedian Hedberg, once called 'next Seinfeld,' dies at 37 April 2, 2005 ST. PAUL, Minn. -- Comedian Mitch Hedberg, whose wide-ranging career included work in nightclubs, television and film, died this week. He was 37. Mr. Hedberg, who struggled with drugs and alcohol, died Wednesday in a hotel room in Livingston, N.J. Pending the medical examiner's report, the cause of death appears to be heart failure, said his mother, Mary Hedberg of St. Paul. She said her son was born with a heart defect and frequently felt anxious about his condition. Mary Hedberg said speculation that her son's death was drug-related was gossip. ''We don't know that for a fact,'' she said, but added, ''it's not a secret Mitch used drugs. Whether that played a role in his death or not, we don't know.'' A hit on ''Late Show With David Letterman,'' on which he appeared 10 times, and ''The Howard Stern Show,'' Mr. Hedberg once was dubbed ''the next Seinfeld'' by Time magazine. But TV-series fame eluded him because his unique style of mumbled one-liners didn't lend itself to the sitcom format. Mr. Hedberg delivered absurdist, random observations in a spacy staccato. His long, dirty blond hair harkened to the image of a 1970s stoner. "Rice is great when you're hungry and you want 2,000 of something," he declared. Another gag surmised, "Foosball is a combination of soccer and shish kebabs." Jokes about Mr. Hedberg's drug use were a staple of his act. He took a hiatus from performing for several months after a May 2003 arrest in Austin, Texas, for felony possession of heroin. Born in St. Paul, Mr. Hedberg rose through the ranks at Minneapolis' Acme Comedy Co. and caught his big break through a Comedy Central special. His rambling, non-sequitur style often drew comparisons to Steven Wright, but Mr. Hedberg disagreed. ''If I made potato chips and put them in a can, people would say I was ripping off Pringles,'' he said. ''But what if I put them in a bag?'' Mr. Hedberg had two popular comedy CDs, ''Strategic Grill Locations'' and ''Mitch All Together.'' He acted in the movie ''Almost Famous'' -- smoking fake pot with Peter Frampton -- and appeared on Fox's hit series ''That '70s Show.'' AP This makes me really sad... Greatest damn stand-up ever. It's a damn shame.

Ended up finishing at a lil' over 9ish. 

Enough of this. I wanna go do somethin, anyone interested innnn.... ... .... Ya know ill let you decide :P

Im done with my boringness of band stories for now.. i think... unless i can remember anything at all that happend this weekend and or during school... Oh ya.

My english teacher asked me why i wasnt in K level classes and i was like uhhhh...... I failed out of them and shes like uh..huh... Another thing... Im learnin ta play da french horn! Go me! I can play uhhh uhhh uhh a c... scale.. ... ... yaaa... hmm... and american riversongs! But only on a melaphone so eh. Oh yes last thing, Football game 'gainst creek. That game fucking owned... 3 ways... 1) The acuall football game just... freakin owned hard ass. 2)I got to see Jaymi Paige Michelle 3) It was the 8th grade game meaning there were 8th graders playing with us in the stands it was pretty tight. I guess one more thing 4) being that uhhh... got to sit by some friends that would acually do stuff, not just bloody sit there and stare blatanly into the giant lights. Oh ya that was coo.

Oh oh oh... Ya theres like this really really really tight game that i found. Its in open beta right now which = no pay of the money yet. One thing though... its in all german. :o otherwise its like totally competly bad ass. And thats where my weekend went i remember now! e_e

K. Woke up at 6 this mornin to get ready for a Bands of America so ya. Got there 30 minutes early with my section to polish our horns... god mines so freakin rusty and shit the polish really really didnt help that much but oh well it looked alot better then it did before ill give it that much. So Venstra's like... ok put on your ponchos we're going outside to march and its raining blah blah blah.. i swear every 15 minutes we were out there he would say... "we're only going to be out here for about another 15 minutes" Ya ok sure why not *shrug* Oh god the busride up there was soooooo fun! So i slept the first 10 minutes of it... what do u want from me i was tired give meh a break :P Kevin let us listen to his dell... ipodish not ipodish thing and it had some coo songs on it ... As soon as we got up the first hill what'a ya know... theres another! How lovely. Arghz0r :P


So the whole time we are doing everything.. Venstra was like "theres no rush." So like we are not rushing... all of a sudden EVERYONE GET IN TEH STADIUM PUT YOUR WHOLE UNIFORM ON NOW GET IN THERE GO GO GO. So im like... WHAT THE HELL! Everyones already walkin in there with their uniform and im still holding everything in my hands. So as we are walkin' down to get our picture taken these ppl had to stamp our hands to get back into the stadium. Ok ... COMMON SENSE NEEDS TO KICK IN RIGHT NOW. Small stamp + Extremly sweaty ppl. Does anyone understand what happend to everyone stamp... im just curious. Anywayz apparently the stamp didnt matter and ill get back to that later. We took a picture as a whole group... seroius ones and unseroius ones blah blah. Then we branch off into sections (only if we wanted to) to get our pictures done that way. I want to huggle it to death for being so coo. Its like hardcore flute and either chello or violein.. my guess is vio but i wouldnt know. Hhahahahah right when it got really really dark outside on the bus charles took out his camera phone and told me to take a picture of something... and i didnt know what to take a pic of so he goes "dude take a pic of toasty" and im like "But its to dark" Hes like just do it so i was like Hey Toasty, he turns and this big ass bright flash goes off right in his face he was like AHHHHH OMG MY EYES! lololol... i didnt know the damn camera had a flash so for the rest of the ride home (bout 45 minutes) just sat there.. flashing ppl in the fause with the camera phone.
